User wants forward-looking guidance signal as the FIRST visible signal
('very good or very bad about future in first line') and finds the
existing 'India Institutional Mode — Sell-side consensus is sparse...'
banner redundant once the verdict card is in place.

A. FORWARD PILL ON TOP LINE
   New 6-class outlook grade rendered next to VERDICT pill:
    very_positive → STRONG (green)
    positive      → POSITIVE (light green)
    mixed         → MIXED (amber)
    cautious      → CAUTIOUS (orange)
    weak          → WEAK (red)
    not_provided  → skipped (no pill rendered)

   Computation combines:
    - Explicit guidance.direction from inferGuidance (raised /
      lowered / maintained / introduced) — strongest signal
    - Concall tone counts (positive / cautious / negative)
    - Topical mention coverage (capex, capacity, launches, demand,
      operating_leverage, customer_wins all flagged as positive
      forward indicators)

   Decision tree:
    raised guidance OR (introduced + ≥3 positive cues) → very_positive
    lowered guidance → weak
    introduced/maintained + ≥2 positive + dominant → positive
    negative-dominant + ≥3 negatives → weak
    cautious-dominant + ≥2 → cautious
    no concall + no guidance language → not_provided

   Evidence string drawn from keyMentions:
    - 'guidance raised by management' / 'guidance lowered by management'
      when explicit
    - else top 3 forward-positive topics joined: 'capacity / capex
      expansion + new launches + demand outlook'
    - else fallback to tone-signal counts: 'N positive signals in
      commentary'

   Renders as a SECOND PILL beside VERDICT in the top-line card,
   followed by a forward-outlook subtitle line:
   '▶ Forward outlook: positive — capacity / capex expansion +
   new launches + demand outlook'

B. BANNER REMOVED
   The 'India Institutional Mode — Sell-side consensus is sparse...'
   yellow banner that appeared between the header and the Latest
   Quarter table is gone. The verdict + FORWARD pill card now
   replaces it as the institutional summary. Saves ~50px of
   vertical space and the explanatory text was redundant.

C. CLEANER HEADER
   Removed the duplicate '🇮🇳 India · Fundamentals Mode' pill from
   the company-name line (the page wrapper above the report
   already shows it once). Header now reads cleaner:
   'Bajaj Consumer Care Ltd  BAJAJCON' instead of 'Bajaj Consumer
   Care Ltd  BAJAJCON  🇮🇳 INDIA · FUNDAMENTALS MODE'.

After this lands, Intellect Design Arena will show:
  [AVOID] [FORWARD: STRONG] QoQ rebound (+15.9%) · OPM compressed 600 bps YoY
  ▶ Forward outlook: strong — new launches + forward guidance
  Deteriorating fundamentals; key issue: cash conversion weak (CFO/PAT 0.22x)
  Watch: CC Revenue Growth · EBIT Margin · Deal TCV

